<p><b>Richard Avedon</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1923-05-15"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="05-15"><a href="/wiki/May_15" title="May 15">May 15</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1923" title="1923">1923</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2004-10-01"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-01"><a href="/wiki/October_1" title="October 1">October 1</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2004" title="2004">2004</a></span>) was an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Photographer" title="Photographer">photographer</a>. Avedon capitalized on his early success in fashion photography and expanded into the realm of <a href="/wiki/Fine_art" title="Fine art">fine art</a>.</p>
